<section>
  <header class="section-head"><div class="wrap"><div class="section-head-inner"><div><div class="section-kicker">The Rulebook</div><h1 class="section-title">Exam System &amp; Rules</h1></div><p class="section-deck">How CCSU LLB examination, credits, and promotion work</p></div></div></header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="rules-grid">
      <div class="rule-item">
        <h2 class="rule-title">Paper Pattern</h2>
        <div class="rule-body">
          <p><strong>Section A:</strong> 5 compulsory short questions × 4 marks = 20 marks</p>
          <p><strong>Section B:</strong> Attempt 2 of 3 × 10 marks = 20 marks</p>
          <p><strong>Section C:</strong> Attempt 3 of 5 × 20 marks = 60 marks</p>
          <p>Total: 100 marks per paper · 3-hour duration</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-item">
        <h2 class="rule-title">Passing Marks</h2>
        <div class="rule-body">
          <p><strong>36 out of 100</strong> (36%) per paper required to pass.</p>
          <p>No aggregate passing — each paper must be cleared individually.</p>
          <p>Total per semester: 5 papers × 100 = 500 marks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-item">
        <h2 class="rule-title">Back Paper Rules</h2>
        <div class="rule-body">
          <p><strong>Fail 1-2 papers:</strong> Promoted to next semester. Clear them as back papers.</p>
          <p><strong>Fail 3+ papers:</strong> Semester back. Repeat the entire semester.</p>
          <p>Back papers can be attempted in the next examination cycle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-item">
        <h2 class="rule-title">Practical Papers</h2>
        <div class="rule-body">
          <p><strong>K-3005</strong> (Sem III): Theory 50 + Project File 30 + Viva 20</p>
          <p><strong>K-4007</strong> (Sem IV): Sessional Diary 40 + Field Work 40 + Viva 20</p>
          <p><strong>K-5005</strong> (Sem V): Theory 50 + Pleading 20 + Conveyancing 20 + Viva 10</p>
          <p><strong>K-6008</strong> (Sem VI): Moot Courts 35 + Court Assignments 25 + Interviewing 20 + Viva 10 + Diary 10</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-item" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <h2 class="rule-title">Optional Subject Selection Guide</h2>
        <div class="rule-body">
          <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--ink-60);margin-bottom:12px;">Three semesters have optional papers. You choose ONE from each group (subject to faculty availability).</p>
          <p><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester II — Choose 1:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>K-2005 Indian Legal & Constitutional History</strong> — narrative-heavy, suits essay writers. Easier to score if you enjoy history.</p>
          <p><strong>K-2006 Law of Taxation</strong> — Income Tax Act sections, computation. More technical but predictable. <em>Most commonly offered.</em></p>
          <p style="margin-top:14px;"><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester IV — Choose 1:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>K-4004 Criminology & Penology</strong> — essay-friendly, theory-heavy. Best for students who write well.</p>
          <p><strong>K-4005 Law of Trust, Equity & Fiduciary Relation</strong> — conceptual. Rarely offered at most colleges.</p>
          <p><strong>K-4006 Banking Law incl. NI Act</strong> — definition and rote-heavy. Easiest to score. <em>Most commonly offered.</em></p>
          <p style="margin-top:14px;"><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester VI — Choose 1:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>K-6004 Intellectual Property Law</strong> — Copyright, Trademarks, Patents. Good for tech/business interest.</p>
          <p><strong>K-6005 IT & Cyber Law</strong> — IT Act 2000, digital signatures, cyber crimes. Contemporary.</p>
          <p><strong>K-6006 Women & Child Law</strong> — 498A, 304B, CEDAW. Socially relevant.</p>
          <p><strong>K-6007 Right to Information</strong> — RTI Act 2005. Compact syllabus. <em>Often easiest to score.</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
